President Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 17-23, 2015 as World Trade Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of trade in America's economic growth and job creation. It emphasizes the need to ensure that all Americans can benefit from trade and that foreign markets are open and fair. The proclamation also discusses the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) agreement, stating that it will open new opportunities for American workers and businesses in the Asia-Pacific region. The TPP aims to update NAFTA, enforce labor and environmental standards, and provide access to markets. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to celebrate and educate themselves about the benefits of trade during World Trade Week.